<caption id="B4B4663DFFF5FE3CFF7AB493291155AC" box="[151,1088,194,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<paragraph id="E07436B5FFF5FE3CFF7AB493291155AC" blockId="3.[151,1088,194,218]" box="[151,1088,194,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="D2BFEAA7FFF5FE3CFF7AB4932DA055AC" bold="true" box="[151,241,194,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Table 1.</emphasis>
Morphometric data of the holotype (H, male) and paratypes of 
<taxonomicName id="27CB4D36FFF5FE3CFC77B492296D55AC" box="[922,1084,195,218]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dapazi">Rivulus dapazi</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="B4B4663DFFF5FE3CFF7AB1FD2C795372" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4647312" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4647312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4647312/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" startId="3.[151,190,1452,1476]" targetBox="[161,794,787,1274]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="E07436B5FFF5FE3CFF7AB1FD2C795372" blockId="3.[151,794,1452,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="D2BFEAA7FFF5FE3CFF7AB1FD2D8A50B2" bold="true" box="[151,219,1452,1476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
Geographic distribution of species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="27CB4D36FFF5FE3CFD26B1FC2E4B50B2" box="[715,794,1453,1476]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2BFEAA7FFF5FE3CFD26B1FC2E4B50B2" box="[715,794,1453,1476]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Rivulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Paraná, Paraguay, and upper Araguaia river basins, central Brazil.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E07436B5FFF5FE3CFF50B2762CB65208" blockId="3.[151,795,1575,1918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Scales large, cycloid. Trunk scaled; head scaled except on anteroventral surface. Body scales slightly extending over caudal-fin base; no scales on dorsal and anal fins. Frontal squamation usually F-patterned, sometimes E-patterned; Escales not overlapping medially; scales arranged in circular pattern around central A-scale without exposed margins. Longitudinal series of scales 34-35; transverse series of scales 8; scale rows around caudal peduncle 16. Contact organs absent. Supraorbital neuromasts 3 + 3. Six branchiostegal rays. Gill rakers of first branchial arch 1 + 7-8. One to three vomerine teeth. Total vertebrae 30-31.</paragraph>
